{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Computer vision tasks relating to human action mainly include action recognition (Tran et al. 2015; Hu et al. 2022b; Wang et al. 2022b), action prediction (Kong and Fu 2022), and temporal action detection (Xia and Zhan 2020).",
    "Important achievements have been made in the field of action recognition in respect of facial recognition (Li et al. 2022b) and video surveillance.",
    "Researchers typically use edited videos for action recognition with only one action.",
    "Therefore, action recognition only needs to classify the action without detecting the duration of the action.",
    "However, most videos in real life are untrimmed and may contain multiple instances of actions in different categories, each with an unknowable time boundary and duration."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Computer vision tasks relating to human action mainly include action recognition (Tran et al. 2015; Hu et al. 2022b; Wang et al. 2022b), action prediction (Kong and Fu 2022), and temporal action detection (Xia and Zhan 2020).",
    "Important achievements have been made in the field of action recognition in respect of facial recognition (Li et al. 2022b) and video surveillance."
  ]
}